<subSubSection pageNumber="502" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageNumber="502">
Brullo (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="502">Webbia</emphasis>
34: 290. 1979) stated that the unspecified Linnaean type was of uncertain identification, and that the name should therefore be treated as ambiguous. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
name has been treated as the basionym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Fourr." authorityName="Fourr." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chiliadenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glutinosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="502">Chiliadenus glutinosus</emphasis>
(L.) Fourr.
</taxonomicName>
but no original elements corresponding with this usage of the name appear to be in existence.
</paragraph>
